{
  "analysis": {
    "summary": "Traced the complete Kafka-Flink streaming data flow architecture across two repositories (Apache Kafka ~1M LOC, Apache Flink ~2M LOC). Mapped the producer/consumer client APIs, Flink's Source/SplitEnumerator framework, connector-base abstractions, serialization boundaries, and checkpoint-offset integration. Identified the three-layer architecture: Kafka transport (bytes, replication, offset commit), Flink connector bridge (KafkaConsumer wrapper, split discovery, state mapping), and Flink core semantics (SourceOperator checkpoint protocol, RecordEmitter watermarks). Detailed how checkpoint barriers trigger offset commits and recovery restores from committed offsets for exactly-once guarantees.",
    "files_examined": [
      {
        "path": "clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/producer/Producer.java",
        "repo": "github.com/sg-benchmarks/kafka--be816b82",
        "description": "Kafka Producer interface: send(ProducerRecord) → Future<RecordMetadata>, flush(), transactional methods (initTransactions, beginTransaction, sendOffsetsToTransaction, commitTransaction)"
      },
      {
        "path": "clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/producer/ProducerRecord.java",
        "repo": "github.com/sg-benchmarks/kafka--be816b82",
        "description": "Data structure: topic, partition (optional), timestamp (optional), key, value, headers. Immutable wrapper for single message to be sent to Kafka."
      },
      {
        "path": "clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/common/serialization/Serializer.java",
        "repo": "github.com/sg-benchmarks/kafka--be816b82",
        "description": "Interface: configure(Map<String,?>, boolean isKey), serialize(String topic, T data) → byte[], serialize(String topic, Headers headers, T data) → byte[]. Stateless contract for type-to-bytes conversion."
      },
      {
        "path": "clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/consumer/Consumer.java",
        "repo": "github.com/sg-benchmarks/kafka--be816b82",
        "description": "Consumer interface: subscribe(Collection<String>), assign(Collection<TopicPartition>), poll(Duration) → ConsumerRecords<K,V>, commitSync(Map<TopicPartition,OffsetAndMetadata>), seek(TopicPartition, long), position(), committed()."
      },
      {
        "path": "clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/consumer/ConsumerRecord.java",
        "repo": "github.com/sg-benchmarks/kafka--be816b82",
        "description": "Data structure: topic, partition, offset, timestamp, timestampType, key, value, headers, serializedKeySize, serializedValueSize, leaderEpoch, deliveryCount. Immutable record received from Kafka."
      },
      {
        "path": "clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/common/serialization/Deserializer.java",
        "repo": "github.com/sg-benchmarks/kafka--be816b82",
        "description": "Interface: configure(Map<String,?>, boolean isKey), deserialize(String topic, byte[] data) → T, deserialize(String topic, Headers, byte[]) → T, deserialize(String topic, Headers, ByteBuffer) → T. Stateless contract for bytes-to-type conversion."
      },
      {
        "path": "clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/consumer/OffsetAndMetadata.java",
        "repo": "github.com/sg-benchmarks/kafka--be816b82",
        "description": "Wraps offset (long), metadata (String), leaderEpoch (Optional<Integer>). Used in Consumer.commitSync(Map<TopicPartition, OffsetAndMetadata>) to persist offsets to __consumer_offsets topic."
      },
      {
        "path": "flink-core-api/src/main/java/org/apache/flink/api/connector/dsv2/Source.java",
        "repo": "github.com/apache/flink",
        "description": "Placeholder interface for DataStream V2 source (experimental). Real implementation uses Source from FLIP-27 (flink-core)."
      },
      {
        "path": "flink-core/src/main/java/org/apache/flink/api/connector/source/SourceReader.java",
        "repo": "github.com/apache/flink",
        "description": "Core interface: start(), pollNext(ReaderOutput<T>) → InputStatus (non-blocking), snapshotState(checkpointId) → List<SplitT>, addSplits(List<SplitT>), notifyNoMoreSplits(), isAvailable() → CompletableFuture<Void>, notifyCheckpointComplete(checkpointId)."
      },
      {
        "path": "flink-core/src/main/java/org/apache/flink/api/connector/source/SplitEnumerator.java",
        "repo": "github.com/apache/flink",
        "description": "Coordinator interface: start(), handleSplitRequest(subtaskId, hostname), addSplitsBack(List<SplitT>, subtaskId), addReader(subtaskId), snapshotState(checkpointId) → CheckpointT, notifyCheckpointComplete(checkpointId), handleSourceEvent(subtaskId, SourceEvent), close()."
      },
      {
        "path": "flink-connectors/flink-connector-base/src/main/java/org/apache/flink/connector/base/source/reader/SourceReaderBase.java",
        "repo": "github.com/apache/flink",
        "description": "Abstract base class implementing SourceReader. Manages SplitFetcherManager (thread pool), FutureCompletingBlockingQueue (buffers elements), RecordEmitter (transforms records). Non-blocking poll loop: fetcher threads push RecordsWithSplitIds → queue, main thread pulls and calls emitRecord()."
      },
      {
        "path": "flink-connectors/flink-connector-base/src/main/java/org/apache/flink/connector/base/source/reader/splitreader/SplitReader.java",
        "repo": "github.com/apache/flink",
        "description": "Interface for reading from splits: fetch() → RecordsWithSplitIds<E> (may block on I/O), handleSplitsChanges(SplitsChange<SplitT>) (non-blocking), wakeUp() (interrupt blocking fetch), pauseOrResumeSplits(Collection<SplitT>, Collection<SplitT>). Implemented per connector (e.g., KafkaSplitReader wraps KafkaConsumer)."
      },
      {
        "path": "flink-connectors/flink-connector-base/src/main/java/org/apache/flink/connector/base/source/reader/RecordEmitter.java",
        "repo": "github.com/apache/flink",
        "description": "Interface: emitRecord(E element, SourceOutput<T> output, SplitStateT splitState) throws Exception. Transforms intermediate element E (from SplitReader) to final type T, emits via SourceOutput (collects with timestamp/watermark), updates mutable split state (e.g., offset tracking)."
      },
      {
        "path": "flink-core/src/main/java/org/apache/flink/api/common/serialization/DeserializationSchema.java",
        "repo": "github.com/apache/flink",
        "description": "Flink serde boundary interface: open(InitializationContext), deserialize(byte[] message) → T, deserialize(byte[], Collector<T> out), isEndOfStream(T) → boolean. Optional second serde layer (after Kafka's Deserializer) for schema evolution, filtering, watermark assignment."
      },
      {
        "path": "flink-runtime/src/main/java/org/apache/flink/streaming/api/operators/SourceOperator.java",
        "repo": "github.com/apache/flink",
        "description": "Runtime operator wrapping SourceReader<OUT, SplitT>. Key methods: snapshotState(StateSnapshotContext) calls sourceReader.snapshotState(checkpointId) and writes to ListState<byte[]>; notifyCheckpointComplete(checkpointId) triggers offset commits; initializeState() restores splits and calls addSplits(); emitNext() polls sourceReader. Integrates with checkpoint protocol for exactly-once semantics."
      }
    ],
    "reasoning": "The Kafka-Flink architecture spans three layers: (1) Kafka transport layer provides ProducerRecord/ConsumerRecord data structures, Serializer/Deserializer interfaces for bytes conversion, Consumer.commitSync() for durable offset commits to __consumer_offsets topic. (2) Flink connector layer (apache/flink-connector-kafka) wraps KafkaConsumer, discovers partitions as SplitEnumerator splits, implements SplitReader to call consumer.poll(), maps Kafka offsets to Flink split state. (3) Flink core layer provides SourceReader/SplitEnumerator abstraction, SourceReaderBase helper with SplitFetcherManager for async fetching, RecordEmitter for timestamp/watermark assignment, SourceOperator for checkpoint integration. The checkpoint-offset integration is critical: SourceOperator.snapshotState() calls SourceReader.snapshotState() which returns List<SplitT> containing current offsets; after checkpoint completes, notifyCheckpointComplete() triggers Consumer.commitSync(Map<TopicPartition, OffsetAndMetadata>) to persist offsets. On recovery, splits are restored and KafkaConsumer.seek() resumes from committed offset. This pattern provides exactly-once semantics: snapshot = next-to-read offset, barrier prevents duplicates in Flink, commit after barrier ensures no re-processing. Dual serialization boundary: Kafka Deserializer<K>/Deserializer<V> converts bytes to typed objects (K, V); Flink DeserializationSchema<T> optionally wraps ConsumerRecord<K,V> for semantic transformation. Thread architecture: SplitFetcherManager runs fetcher threads calling SplitReader.fetch() (blocking on I/O), results enqueued to FutureCompletingBlockingQueue, main task thread calls SourceReader.pollNext() (non-blocking) to drain queue and emit records via RecordEmitter."
  }
}

