  "analysis": {
    "summary": "Traced the complete Kafka-Flink streaming data flow architecture across two repositories (Apache Kafka ~1M LOC, Apache Flink ~2M LOC). Mapped the producer/consumer client APIs, Flink's Source/SplitEnumerator framework, connector-base abstractions, serialization boundaries, and checkpoint-offset integration. Identified the three-layer architecture: Kafka transport (bytes, replication, offset commit), Flink connector bridge (KafkaConsumer wrapper, split discovery, state mapping), and Flink core semantics (SourceOperator checkpoint protocol, RecordEmitter watermarks). Detailed how checkpoint barriers trigger offset commits and recovery restores from committed offsets for exactly-once guarantees.",
